Architecture plan for Issue #23: Change the app background to green

Project shape:
- Single Vite + React + TypeScript frontend application.
- Main shell component lives in src/App.tsx and composes calculator behavior/hooks with CalculatorCard.
- Calculator state and behavior remain isolated in src/calculator/*; presentational UI remains in src/components/*.
- Styling is Tailwind utility classes applied directly in JSX, with the full-screen page background controlled by the <main> element in src/App.tsx.

Implementation plan:
- Update only src/App.tsx for the feature issue by changing the full-screen <main> background utility from the current light neutral tone to Tailwind green-100 (or closest equivalent).
- Leave CalculatorCard, calculator hooks, text colors, spacing, and all calculator behavior unchanged.
- No shared type changes or dependency changes are required.

Validation plan:
- Run the existing unit/e2e/build checks available in package.json as appropriate for the issue session.
- Since existing tests validate layout/behavior rather than exact background color, expected test changes are none.

Issue dependency notes:
- There is only one remaining issue (#23), so there are no inter-issue dependencies.
